VSensuously sparkling recital
p3
sVnews
p4
VExquisitely accompanied on mridangam by Vankayala Venkataramana Murty and G. Venkata Rao on ghatam, it was rendered for Visakha Music Academy.Getting off to a tuneful start with theSri Varalakshmi(Sri raga) of Dikshitar, the duo sharing the expression of the manodharma (ragam and swaram)in equal measure, exquisitely elaboratedSamajavaragamana(Hindolam),Yenduku Srirama(Saaranga),Bhajare Re Maanasa(Carnataka Devagandhari) andGnanamosagarada(Poorvikalyani) before going in for an expansive expatiation ofPankajalochana(Kalyani) adorned with tanam and neravu as well.Winner for the best veena performance award of the Madras Music Academy and Srikrishna Gaanasabha of Chennai besides being a choice for the conferment of titles &#8216;Veena Vaadya Vidya Visarada&#8217;, &#8216;Sunaada Sudhanidhi&#8217; and the like by prestigious sabhas in the country and Mahati Kalaanidhi by the Ajo Vibho Kandalam Foundation, U.S.A., Syamasundaram no wonder was the cynosure in Kalabharathi.Rendering of a tarangamDevadideva(Sindhubhairavi),Vandanamu Raghunandana(Sahana),Kshetrayya padhamin Saveri and finally a composition of Ramadass inNaadanamakriyamarked the concluding session.
